{"word":"ἴδρις","slug":"ἴδρις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἴδρις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἴδμεν</el> II\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>experienced, knowing, skilful</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>knowing how</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἴδρις</el> alone, <i>the provident one</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>the ant</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}